The `btManifoldResult::addContactPoint` function can call `btPersistentManifold::replaceContactPoint`. When it does, `gContactAddedCallback` may be called but `gtContactDestroyed` will not be called. Instead, the user data from the old contact point is retained and the new point will point to the user data of the old point. Is this intentional? I ask because I am setting the user data in the "contact added" callback and deleting the user data in the "contact destroyed" callback. I therefore expect the "contact destroyed" callback to be called regardless of whether the manifold point is destroyed or replaced.

I also notice the following block of code in `replaceContactPoint`, which appears to be redundant:
```
m_pointCache[insertIndex].m_appliedImpulse = appliedImpulse;
m_pointCache[insertIndex].m_appliedImpulseLateral1 = appliedLateralImpulse1;
m_pointCache[insertIndex].m_appliedImpulseLateral2 = appliedLateralImpulse2;
	
m_pointCache[insertIndex].m_appliedImpulse =  appliedImpulse;
m_pointCache[insertIndex].m_appliedImpulseLateral1 = appliedLateralImpulse1;
m_pointCache[insertIndex].m_appliedImpulseLateral2 = appliedLateralImpulse2;
```

